This is still an issue. Here is a simple example:

```
module circular-bug {

    yang-version 1;

    namespace "http://bug.com/circular-bug";

    prefix cbug;

    organization "foo";

    contact      "foo";

    description  "Demonstrate circular bug."; 

    revision 2017-03-31 {
        description "Initial revision";
        reference "none";
    }

    typedef circular-type {
        description "Generates a circular dependency warning!";
        type enumeration {
            enum item {
                description "blah";
            }
        }
    }

    typedef non-circular-type {
        type enumeration {
            enum item {
                description "blah";
            }
        }
        description "Doesn't generate a circular dependency warning!";
    }

    leaf circular {
        type circular-type;
        description "blah";
    }

    leaf non-circular {
        type non-circular-type;
        description "blah";
    }
}
```

Current release of pyang generates this output with this module:

```
09:05 $ pyang --lint circular-bug.yang
circular-bug.yang:20: error: circular dependency for type "circular-type"
circular-bug.yang:21: error: keyword "description" not in canonical order,expected "type", (See RFC 6020, Section 12)
circular-bug.yang:22: error: keyword "type" not in canonical order, (See RFC 6020, Section 12)
09:06 $ pyang --version
pyang 1.7.1
```

you can create some "virtual" task, and submit 10k each time. and set detail page priority higher than the virtual task. pyspider will automatically load next 10k links after detail page job finished.

```
def on_start(self):
    for i in range(100):
        self.crawl('data:;fake_url_%s' % i, save=i, callback=self.load_urls)

@config(priority=0)
def load_urls(self, response):
    for url in self.database.get(offset=response.save * 10000, limit=10000):
        self.crawl(url, callback=self.detail_page)

@config(priority=1)
def detail_page(self):
    pass
