This is a bug of the backend. You should be able to specify not only a timezone-naive datetime object but also a timezone-aware one as a default value for DateTimeField even if it is mapped to a legacy `datetime` type column.

I have pushed the new version of the backend that contains the changes for this issue to PyPI. Please let me know if you still have the same error after updating the backend to the new one.

@venkates, long time but worthwhile to mention, even for future searches.  
With, recently merged, string escape option you can now override utf-8 decoding attempts. Using `--escape raw` will pass bytes as is, avoiding any decode attempt.  It will still be `\uXXXX` escaped but with raw values.

