As a workaround (in addition to nabilfreeman's html-based solution), you could do it with html *AND CSS*

![Screenshot][0]



```css
.snooze {
  position: relative;
  font-size: 14px;
  user-select: none;
  font-family: sans-serif;
  width: 24px;
  height: 16px;
  padding-top: 9px;
  padding-left: 1px;
}
.snooze::before {
  content: "Z";
  position: absolute;
  font-size: 10px;
  left: 11px;
  top: 3px;
}
.snooze::after {
  content: "Z";
  position: absolute;
  font-size: 7px;
  left: 19px;
  top: -1px;
  font-weight: bold;
}
```



This might offer a little more customization than Plain Old HTML, and also you could keep the markup pretty consistent with other `<i class="fa fa-something"><i>` elements

