@syrusakbary 
I solved the issue. Graphene is fine. The problem was in the Apollo client, because  Apollo cannot determine the IDs to use for object. There is a `dataIdFromObject` function for that purpose. I took this peace of code from the Apollo tutorial:
```
const client = new ApolloClient({
  dataIdFromObject: o => o.id
});
```

But I have several Django models with the same ids, so it caused the problem with typename of objects.

Changing the code to this is solved the problem:

```
const client = new ApolloClient({
  dataIdFromObject: o => `${o.__typename}-${o.id},`
});
```

